test_method_1 = Observe the mushroom's habitat — morel mushrooms typically grow near trees with shallow soil;
test_method_2 = Minutes after ingestion if the mushroom taste is mildly earthy or bitter, that's normal;
test_method_3 = Visual inspection by using a magnifying glass to check for the presence of gills, which morel mushrooms always have;
safety_warning = Some foods may have been added to the mushrooms to encourage eating;
recommendation = If in doubt, taste a small amount — if the taste feels normal and appears similar to what you've seen online images of, then the mushrooms are likely safe to eat.
